It emphasizes the importance of bat control before taking up maintenance activities on the property, as the unwanted destruction of a single breeding and birth site can kill up to 400 females and young, and even destroy the entire local population.
Bats are protected and killing, disrupting or destroying them is illegal.
Scottish officer Elisabeth Ferrell of the Bat Defence League has urged the public to contribute.
